<subSubSection id="E339CF4A856C030E1C0CBDA734BEC8CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="host">
<paragraph id="84592027B5AE81EB5CC2ADDA05C81518" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Hosts.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FD17A7BCC99ACA2AC138A0B1DCDD6AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicName id="5FB57F4B9DC0F5CF25C212E43A7825E3" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1783" class="Insecta" family="Coreidae" genus="Homoeocerus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Homoeocerus unipunctatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unipunctatus">
<emphasis id="77C936E0318C6D7B9B282C18AB0A9B84" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Homoeocerus unipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Thunberg, 1783) (
<taxonomicName id="09B3BB8158C176700829E790F1EA61B5" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Alydidae</taxonomicName>
) feeding on 
<taxonomicName id="CB18E4BE2B19E1854476DADAD41D43A5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pueraria" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pueraria lobata" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="0AC3818100D8A3FA8A57494BD13575C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Pueraria lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="0FD25F41CBD4A62CF98F7EA18360FA77" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Pueraria" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="BFC20909F7F22700D182898E21283DB6" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Riptortus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Riptortus pedestris" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedestris">
<emphasis id="93EF00C1A7BE8585FD904E42EC82E729" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Riptortus pedestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1758) (
<taxonomicName id="1467B8913B04AA9EE8A6A1F3F5CA8447" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Alydidae</taxonomicName>
) on 
<taxonomicName id="F2160E8CC3A76236D4B2D09F3B7B3871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Phaseolus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phaseolus vulgaris" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="663B712311B834BEE7841EFAFEFDF58C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Phaseolus vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="56E65E9DB7838212B0CBE9153E26FD9E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Phaseolus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) (both new records). The family 
<taxonomicName id="BADE723C4988014B63344817B8E24B67" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Alydidae</taxonomicName>
is the first record of the host of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8E44C8BA96EFB091F0655FCB2339FFF5" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2C0DD9BEBA8B0CFFEE444A5D61D7966F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BEEB46CAB35904E571CCB116CA37CDC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C828CEBCBFD94510C673114276934F17" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="62E0C980D477CA29A4B0DBDEC495FDDC" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
The female specimens examined agree well with the redescription by 
<bibRefCitation id="AF9A7E614F91F9B8DCC528B33864B371" author="Chou, LY" journalOrPublisher="Special publications" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="19 - 39" refId="B6" refString="Chou, LY, 1987. The genus Aridelus of Taiwan (Hymenoptera: Braconidae: Euphorinae) Taiwan Agricultural Research Institute. Special publications 22: 19 - 39" title="The genus Aridelus of Taiwan (Hymenoptera: Braconidae: Euphorinae) Taiwan Agricultural Research Institute." volume="22" year="1987">Chou (1987)</bibRefCitation>
and that in the key by 
<bibRefCitation id="18EFF7E79F6F95172758C795340472BE" author="Chen, XX" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 217" refId="B5" refString="Chen, XX, van Achterberg, C, 1997. Revision of the subfamily Euphorinae (excluding the tribe Meteorini Cresson) (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) from China. Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 313: 1 - 217" title="Revision of the subfamily Euphorinae (excluding the tribe Meteorini Cresson) (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) from China." volume="313" year="1997">Chen and van Achterberg (1997)</bibRefCitation>
; they differ slightly by having the body length 4.1-5.3 mm (4.2-5.1 mm in the previous redescriptions) and the penultimate antennal segment 1.1-1.6
<normalizedToken id="39835F521D88CDE298BC148C7DC3C88F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (1.2-1.6
<normalizedToken id="3F6FE7828DAF12AD481892C0BCEFC771" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
in the redescriptions).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
